cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of data-driven methods to improve patient engagement in care management, which has implications for society and healthcare systems.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses machine learning techniques to develop a scoring method for patient engagement.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper focuses on developing a scoring pipeline using real-world data.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the role of care managers in engaging patients and the use of the scoring method to provide interpretable insights to care managers.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper applies computational methods to healthcare data.
